OL,6,FA complainant said the ad objectified
OL,7,Fand sexualised women and was
OL,8,Foffensive, harmful and irresponsible.
OL,10,FGreat Grass told the Advertising
OL,11,FStandards Authority (ASA) that the ad
OL,12,Fhad been on display for several
OL,13,Fmonths, claiming they had received 47
OL,14,Fpositive comments about it and
OL,15,Fsuggesting it had not offended most of
OL,16,Fthe "hundreds of thousands" of people
OL,17,Fwho had seen it given there had only
OL,18,Fbeen one complaint.
