OL,6,FThe firm said it was wrong to assume
OL,7,Fthat the person featured in the ad was
OL,8,Fa woman when it could "equally be a
OL,9,Fman or a transgender person".
OL,11,F75Media, who owned the poster site,
OL,12,Fsaid it took the ASA's concerns "very
OL,13,Fseriously" and would remove the ad
OL,14,Fimmediately if it was found to breach
OL,15,Fadvertising rules.
