OL,4,Cbanned for objectifying women
OL,6,FThe ASA said those who saw the ad
OL,7,Fwould interpret the image as featuring
OL,8,Fa woman, due to her slim waist, curved
OL,9,Fhips, slim arms and lack of obvious
OL,10,Fbody hair, while the image of the pot
OL,11,Fplant placed over the groin area and
OL,12,Fthe text would be understood as an
OL,13,Fallusion both to pruning a plant and
OL,14,Fto trimming pubic hair.
OL,16,FThe ASA said many people would see the
OL,17,Fad as a light-hearted reference to the
OL,18,Flow maintenance properties of
OL,19,Fartificial grass.
