OL,6,FBut it added: "We considered, however,
OL,7,Fthat the cropped image of a woman in
OL,8,Funderwear accompanied by text that
OL,9,Falluded to pubic hair had the effect
OL,10,Fof demeaning and objectifying women by
OL,11,Fusing their genitalia to draw
OL,12,Fattention to an unrelated product.
OL,14,F"We considered that the emoji next to
OL,15,Fthe text, which featured a winking
OL,16,Fface with its tongue out, added to the
OL,17,Fdegrading and mocking tone.
