OL,3,CSecond ad for artificial grass firm
OL,4,Cbanned for objectifying women
OL,6,F"Because we considered the ad
OL,7,Fobjectified women, we further
OL,8,Fconsidered it was likely to cause
OL,9,Fserious and widespread offence and
OL,10,Fincluded a gender stereotype in a way
OL,11,Fthat was likely to cause harm. We
OL,12,Fconcluded that the ad was
OL,13,Firresponsible and breached the code."
OL,15,FIt ruled that the ad must not appear
OL,16,Fagain, adding: "We told Great Grass to
OL,17,Fensure their future ads were socially
OL,18,Fresponsible and did not cause serious
OL,19,For widespread offence, including by
OL,20,Ffeaturing a harmful gender stereotype
OL,21,Fby objectifying women."
